WEBVTT

1
00:00:09.183 --> 00:00:10.363
[Boyd] Previously onFrom...

2
00:00:10.488 --> 00:00:12.318
[Kenny] I feel like I'm hanging
on by a thread here.

3
00:00:13.491 --> 00:00:15.451
[Sobbing]
Those things. they never run.

4
00:00:15.580 --> 00:00:18.410
They know there's only
so many places we can go.

5
00:00:18.540 --> 00:00:21.500
I think we're running out of
spaces on the board. Sheriff.

6
00:00:21.630 --> 00:00:23.370
I wish you had the luxury of
grief. but you don't. Boyd.

7
00:00:23.501 --> 00:00:26.371
These people need you.

8
00:00:26.504 --> 00:00:29.294
You need to be the one
to lead these people home.

9
00:00:29.420 --> 00:00:31.810
'Cause if you don't.
she died for nothing.

10
00:00:31.944 --> 00:00:33.734
[Boyd] Come on.

11
00:00:33.859 --> 00:00:35.949
Started getting tremors
in my hand a few weeks back.

12
00:00:36.079 --> 00:00:39.389
which means the clock
is officially ticking.

13
00:00:39.517 --> 00:00:41.517
but I have this crazy idea
that might actually work and--

14
00:00:41.650 --> 00:00:43.480
and if it does.

15
00:00:43.608 --> 00:00:46.738
I might be able to find a way
to get these people home.

16
00:00:46.872 --> 00:00:49.832
Something here is missing.
We just can't see it yet.

17
00:00:49.962 --> 00:00:51.232
I need something to write with.

18
00:00:51.355 --> 00:00:54.575
Ask every question. right?

19
00:00:54.706 --> 00:00:56.316
[Jade]
I don't just sit around

20
00:00:56.447 --> 00:00:58.877
fucking accepting the world
as it is!

21
00:00:59.015 --> 00:01:00.885
-[Radio static]
-Someone is doing this.

22
00:01:01.017 --> 00:01:02.627
and I'm not gonna rest
until I figure out how.

23
00:01:02.758 --> 00:01:03.888
[Kenny] Jade!

24
00:01:04.020 --> 00:01:08.160
[Gasping rapidly]

25
00:01:08.285 --> 00:01:10.415
I really like you.

26
00:01:10.548 --> 00:01:14.338
and what's about to happen.
it's gonna save everyone.

27
00:01:14.465 --> 00:01:16.335
[Ethan] Where's my mom?
I want my mom!

28
00:01:16.467 --> 00:01:18.207
You're doing this for her!

29
00:01:18.339 --> 00:01:20.249
Let him go.

30
00:01:20.384 --> 00:01:21.604
They told me this
was the last one.

31
00:01:21.733 --> 00:01:23.213
then everyone gets to go home!

32
00:01:23.344 --> 00:01:24.564
[Grunts]

33
00:01:24.693 --> 00:01:25.783
-Ethan. run!
-No!

34
00:01:25.911 --> 00:01:27.701
You don't understand!

35
00:01:27.826 --> 00:01:29.696
-Nathan!
-Nathan.

36
00:01:29.828 --> 00:01:30.698
Nathan. please!

37
00:01:33.745 --> 00:01:35.615
[Jim] Where is she?

38
00:01:35.747 --> 00:01:37.227
She ran off into the woods.

39
00:01:37.358 --> 00:01:39.448
And?

40
00:01:39.577 --> 00:01:42.277
And if she comes back before
dark. then we'll handle it.

41
00:01:42.406 --> 00:01:44.446
And if she doesn't?

42
00:01:44.582 --> 00:01:46.852
If she doesn't.
then it's handled.

43
00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:54.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

44
00:01:57.073 --> 00:02:01.513
[Shovel thudding]

45
00:02:01.643 --> 00:02:08.353
♪

46
00:02:08.476 --> 00:02:12.436
[Father Khatri] Chaos and faith.

47
00:02:12.567 --> 00:02:15.957
that is the duality
of our existence.

48
00:02:16.092 --> 00:02:18.492
from the moment we first arrive.

49
00:02:18.616 --> 00:02:21.706
and not simply
here in this town...

50
00:02:23.926 --> 00:02:27.796
...but in this world.
in this life.

51
00:02:27.930 --> 00:02:30.670
From the moment
we open our newborn eyes.

52
00:02:30.802 --> 00:02:35.502
we are faced with a chaos we
cannot even begin to understand.

53
00:02:35.633 --> 00:02:38.033
And how do we respond?

54
00:02:38.158 --> 00:02:41.638
What is the very
first sound we make?

55
00:02:41.770 --> 00:02:43.550
We cry out.

56
00:02:44.947 --> 00:02:48.167
We plead for answers.

57
00:02:48.298 --> 00:02:51.908
before we even have words to
give voice to the questions.

58
00:02:53.216 --> 00:02:56.566
That's how we begin our
journey through this world -

59
00:02:56.698 --> 00:02:58.568
terrified.

60
00:02:58.700 --> 00:03:01.960
confused.

61
00:03:02.094 --> 00:03:04.974
And so. we search.
and we strive.

62
00:03:05.097 --> 00:03:07.877
and we stumble
through the chaos.

63
00:03:08.013 --> 00:03:12.503
We spend our lives looking
for signs that somewhere.

64
00:03:12.627 --> 00:03:15.977
somehow there's a meaning.

65
00:03:16.108 --> 00:03:19.628
a purpose to it all.

66
00:03:19.764 --> 00:03:22.904
And then. one day.
we find our faith.

67
00:03:24.204 --> 00:03:27.864
Our faith that we are
each here in this world.

68
00:03:27.990 --> 00:03:30.080
in this place.

69
00:03:30.210 --> 00:03:34.040
as part of God's
mysterious plan.

70
00:03:34.170 --> 00:03:38.780
In our faith. we understand
the chaos is the meaning.

71
00:03:38.914 --> 00:03:41.184
It is in our struggle.

72
00:03:41.308 --> 00:03:44.568
in our search.
that we find our purpose.

73
00:03:48.140 --> 00:03:51.060
"Trust in the Lord
with all thine heart

74
00:03:51.187 --> 00:03:53.317
and lean not unto thine
own understanding."

75
00:03:56.105 --> 00:03:57.885
-Amen.
-[Congregants] Amen.

76
00:04:07.595 --> 00:04:10.025
[Chattering indistinctly]

77
00:04:10.162 --> 00:04:13.212
It's always-- it's always nice
to see new faces.

78
00:04:13.340 --> 00:04:16.820
Yeah. I'm. um--
I just came by to give you this.

79
00:04:18.910 --> 00:04:21.780
We've been packing up
the other family's stuff.

80
00:04:21.913 --> 00:04:24.703
I figured
they were yours.

81
00:04:24.829 --> 00:04:27.439
Yeah.

82
00:04:27.571 --> 00:04:30.711
How's Ethan doing?

83
00:04:30.835 --> 00:04:33.055
Well. he's. um...

84
00:04:33.185 --> 00:04:36.225
He's scared
and confused.

85
00:04:36.363 --> 00:04:38.413
He doesn't understand why
Sara would try to hurt him.

86
00:04:38.539 --> 00:04:39.369
Mm.

87
00:04:41.019 --> 00:04:42.669
Has anyone seen her?

88
00:04:42.804 --> 00:04:45.074
Not since she ran
off into the woods.

89
00:04:45.197 --> 00:04:46.677
Mm.

90
00:04:46.808 --> 00:04:48.768
I ran after her. but...

91
00:04:48.897 --> 00:04:51.807
my knees aren't quite what
they used to be. I'm afraid.

92
00:04:52.727 --> 00:04:55.687
Do you think
she's still alive?

93
00:04:55.817 --> 00:04:57.117
It's unlikely
she survived the night.

94
00:04:57.253 --> 00:05:00.523
Those Bible passages. did you--

95
00:05:00.648 --> 00:05:02.948
did you write
those from memory?

96
00:05:03.085 --> 00:05:06.995
Yeah.
Word for word.

97
00:05:07.132 --> 00:05:09.052
It tends to stick.

98
00:05:12.964 --> 00:05:16.974
Um. what did you really come
here to ask me. Tabitha?

99
00:05:18.100 --> 00:05:19.970
[Exhales]

100
00:05:24.715 --> 00:05:26.455
How do you know
any of this is real?

101
00:05:28.719 --> 00:05:31.159
I mean...
[Exhaling sharply]

102
00:05:31.287 --> 00:05:34.067
It sounds crazy.
but are we dead? Are we alive?

103
00:05:34.203 --> 00:05:36.513
I...
[Sighing]

104
00:05:37.772 --> 00:05:40.042
Would it matter?

105
00:05:40.165 --> 00:05:43.125
I mean. for argument's sake.
let's say we're dead.

106
00:05:43.255 --> 00:05:45.685
and we're all stuck here
together in some strange.

107
00:05:45.823 --> 00:05:47.223
tormented purgatory.

108
00:05:47.347 --> 00:05:51.827
What would be different?
We'd still be stuck.

109
00:05:51.960 --> 00:05:53.960
We'd still be searching
for a way to go home.

110
00:05:54.092 --> 00:05:58.142
All that would change is
the home we're searching for.

111
00:05:58.270 --> 00:06:00.660
Yeah.

112
00:06:00.795 --> 00:06:02.615
I mean. I'm guessing
I'm not the first person

113
00:06:02.753 --> 00:06:04.023
to come to you
with that question.

114
00:06:04.146 --> 00:06:05.836
Well. let's just say

115
00:06:05.974 --> 00:06:07.764
I've had plenty of chances
to work on my answer.

116
00:06:07.889 --> 00:06:09.059
Yeah.

117
00:06:10.021 --> 00:06:12.331
But if it's any
consolation to you.

118
00:06:12.459 --> 00:06:15.849
you were already here
when your vehicle crashed.

119
00:06:15.984 --> 00:06:19.904
You're alive. Tabitha.
Your family's alive.

120
00:06:20.031 --> 00:06:22.691
So you can scratch that
question off your list.

121
00:06:25.080 --> 00:06:27.000
Yeah.

122
00:06:27.125 --> 00:06:28.125
Bye.

123
00:06:28.257 --> 00:06:29.127
Yeah.

124
00:06:30.564 --> 00:06:40.444
♪

125
00:07:05.860 --> 00:07:06.730
[Match scratching]

126
00:07:50.426 --> 00:07:52.466
We need to talk.

127
00:07:56.954 --> 00:08:01.574
["Que Sera. Sera [Whatever Will
Be. Will be]" plays]

128
00:08:01.698 --> 00:08:06.958
♪

129
00:08:07.095 --> 00:08:11.795
♪ When I was
just a little boy♪

130
00:08:11.926 --> 00:08:14.146
♪ I asked my father♪

131
00:08:14.276 --> 00:08:16.496
♪ "What will I be?"♪

132
00:08:17.801 --> 00:08:20.201
♪ "Will I be handsome?"♪

133
00:08:20.325 --> 00:08:22.755
♪ "Will I be rich?"♪

134
00:08:22.893 --> 00:08:25.813
♪ Here's what he said to me♪

135
00:08:27.158 --> 00:08:30.208
♪ "Que sera. sera"♪

136
00:08:30.335 --> 00:08:33.815
♪ "Whatever will be. will be"♪

137
00:08:36.603 --> 00:08:40.043
♪ "The future's
Not ours to see"♪

138
00:08:40.171 --> 00:08:43.571
♪ "Que sera. sera"♪

139
00:08:45.220 --> 00:08:47.830
♪ "What will be. will be"♪

140
00:08:57.624 --> 00:09:02.244
♪ Now
I have children of my own♪

141
00:09:02.367 --> 00:09:04.757
♪ They ask their father♪

142
00:09:04.892 --> 00:09:06.982
♪ "What will I be?♪

143
00:09:08.548 --> 00:09:10.808
♪ "Will I be pretty?"♪

144
00:09:10.941 --> 00:09:13.251
♪ "Will I be rich?"♪

145
00:09:13.378 --> 00:09:15.558
♪ I tell them tenderly♪

146
00:09:18.383 --> 00:09:20.733
♪ "Que sera. sera"♪

147
00:09:20.864 --> 00:09:25.784
♪ "Whatever will be. will be"♪

148
00:09:25.913 --> 00:09:30.703
♪ "The future's
Not ours to see"♪

149
00:09:30.831 --> 00:09:32.961
♪ "Que sera. sera"♪

150
00:09:35.966 --> 00:09:38.356
♪ "What will be. will be"♪

151
00:09:40.536 --> 00:09:42.576
♪ "Que sera. sera"♪

152
00:10:01.339 --> 00:10:03.169
You all right?

153
00:10:03.298 --> 00:10:05.338
Yeah. it--

154
00:10:05.474 --> 00:10:08.834
I'm having a hard time wrapping
my brain around it. I guess.

155
00:10:08.956 --> 00:10:11.386
I mean. it's Sara. you know?

156
00:10:11.523 --> 00:10:14.923
She was always
so thoughtful. so nice.

157
00:10:15.049 --> 00:10:17.969
-How's your mom taking it?
-It's hard.

158
00:10:18.095 --> 00:10:21.705
You know. Sara was kind of like
the daughter she never had.

159
00:10:24.580 --> 00:10:27.410
I been thinking about
what you said the other day.

160
00:10:27.539 --> 00:10:29.799
about running out
of room on the board.

161
00:10:29.933 --> 00:10:30.933
[Kenny]
I was upset.

162
00:10:31.065 --> 00:10:33.935
Well. it doesn't
mean you're wrong.

163
00:10:34.068 --> 00:10:36.848
Something's changing here.
It's like...

164
00:10:36.984 --> 00:10:38.994
like something's slipping away.

165
00:10:39.116 --> 00:10:42.246
The other night. the talisman
worked out in the RV.

166
00:10:42.380 --> 00:10:44.210
same way it does in the houses.

167
00:10:44.339 --> 00:10:46.379
And?

168
00:10:46.515 --> 00:10:48.645
And I've been thinking
that the only reason

169
00:10:48.778 --> 00:10:51.608
we haven't pushed
further into the forest

170
00:10:51.738 --> 00:10:54.388
is we didn't know
whether the talisman

171
00:10:54.523 --> 00:10:56.793
would protect us out there the
same way it does in the town.

172
00:10:58.396 --> 00:10:59.916
So...

173
00:11:00.050 --> 00:11:01.880
I'm putting
together some supplies.

174
00:11:02.009 --> 00:11:03.579
I'm gonna take the talisman

175
00:11:03.706 --> 00:11:06.796
and go out in the forest
and I'm gonna see--

176
00:11:06.927 --> 00:11:09.407
Hey!
Hey. hey. hey. hey!

177
00:11:09.538 --> 00:11:11.368
Kenny. what...

178
00:11:11.496 --> 00:11:14.456
Hey! You don't walk away
when I'm talking to you!

179
00:11:14.586 --> 00:11:15.936
Are you going alone?

180
00:11:16.066 --> 00:11:17.286
Yeah.

181
00:11:17.415 --> 00:11:19.325
And how far are you going?

182
00:11:19.461 --> 00:11:20.941
As far as it'll take me.

183
00:11:21.071 --> 00:11:23.421
I'm doin' this
to find a way out.

184
00:11:23.552 --> 00:11:26.562
find a way home.
Isn't that the point?

185
00:11:26.686 --> 00:11:27.376
Make sure we
all get home?

186
00:11:27.512 --> 00:11:28.952
Honestly?

187
00:11:29.079 --> 00:11:32.039
I'm not sure there
is a point anymore.

188
00:11:32.169 --> 00:11:34.909
But if you're in that much
of a hurry to fuckin' die.

189
00:11:35.042 --> 00:11:36.962
you should just go and do it.

190
00:11:37.087 --> 00:11:38.827
Okay?

191
00:11:49.230 --> 00:11:50.450
[Sighing]
I got everything packed up.

192
00:11:50.579 --> 00:11:51.969
It's ready to go to storage.

193
00:11:52.102 --> 00:11:54.712
Oh. okay.

194
00:11:56.411 --> 00:11:57.721
What are you up to?

195
00:12:00.937 --> 00:12:01.807
Look.

196
00:12:06.029 --> 00:12:07.339
There's no wire in here.

197
00:12:07.465 --> 00:12:08.505
What?

198
00:12:08.640 --> 00:12:10.990
In the cord.

199
00:12:11.121 --> 00:12:13.121
When you want
to splice a wire.

200
00:12:13.254 --> 00:12:14.654
you gotta strip away the coating
to get at the wire inside.

201
00:12:14.777 --> 00:12:17.477
But there's no wire.
This is...

202
00:12:17.606 --> 00:12:18.906
You know.
it's not actually a wire.

203
00:12:19.042 --> 00:12:20.962
And the plug?

204
00:12:21.088 --> 00:12:22.788
Look.

205
00:12:22.916 --> 00:12:25.656
Look.

206
00:12:25.788 --> 00:12:28.968
The outlets.
none of it makes any sense.

207
00:12:29.096 --> 00:12:30.446
I mean. these lamps.
they shouldn't work.

208
00:12:30.575 --> 00:12:32.185
Hello!

209
00:12:32.316 --> 00:12:34.186
Ah. you. uh.
rollercoaster guy.

210
00:12:34.318 --> 00:12:36.708
-I need your help.
-You don't knock?

211
00:12:36.843 --> 00:12:38.763
I'm sorry. would you like me
to take off my shoes too?

212
00:12:38.888 --> 00:12:41.108
You noticed the wire thing too.
huh? Fucking weird. right?

213
00:12:41.238 --> 00:12:43.888
You're that asshole
that almost killed us.

214
00:12:45.808 --> 00:12:47.978
Okay. look. first of all.
I wasn't driving.

215
00:12:48.115 --> 00:12:50.065
Second. my best friend.

216
00:12:50.204 --> 00:12:52.124
who I've known since fourth
grade. is dead. All right?

217
00:12:52.249 --> 00:12:54.299
He's not walking around with
A little boo-boo on his leg.

218
00:12:54.425 --> 00:12:56.295
So. how about we
just call that one even. okay?

219
00:12:56.427 --> 00:12:59.647
Now. you guys wanna play house
or do you wanna go home?

220
00:12:59.779 --> 00:13:01.819
Because I have an idea.

221
00:13:04.696 --> 00:13:06.306
Did you know there's
not a single copy

222
00:13:06.437 --> 00:13:09.477
of the Bible in town?

223
00:13:09.614 --> 00:13:12.794
I mean. in our little
traveler's library in the diner.

224
00:13:12.922 --> 00:13:16.972
there's at least a dozen Robert
Ludlum and Judy Blume novels.

225
00:13:17.100 --> 00:13:19.580
yet...

226
00:13:19.711 --> 00:13:22.281
not a single copy of
the world's most popular book.

227
00:13:28.372 --> 00:13:30.812
I imagine you wonder
why you're here.

228
00:13:32.507 --> 00:13:35.287
You've done such
unspeakable things.

229
00:13:39.775 --> 00:13:42.515
And by the rules of the town.
you should be in the box.

230
00:13:52.657 --> 00:13:54.217
Nathan told me
about the voices.

231
00:13:59.099 --> 00:14:00.619
It's okay.

232
00:14:07.411 --> 00:14:12.331
Sara. what if I
were to tell you

233
00:14:12.460 --> 00:14:16.290
that despite the horrible
things you've done.

234
00:14:16.420 --> 00:14:19.470
you can still help
the people of this town?

235
00:14:19.597 --> 00:14:23.117
You could still
do something good.

236
00:14:23.253 --> 00:14:26.343
I think Nathan would
like that. don't you?

237
00:14:27.649 --> 00:14:28.519
Yeah?

238
00:14:31.174 --> 00:14:32.484
Good.

239
00:14:38.616 --> 00:14:40.006
Those are pretty.

240
00:14:40.140 --> 00:14:41.450
Right?

241
00:14:41.576 --> 00:14:42.786
You have a good eye.
Miss Matthews.

242
00:14:42.925 --> 00:14:44.185
Oh. I just found
them like this.

243
00:14:44.318 --> 00:14:45.668
Like what?

244
00:14:45.797 --> 00:14:47.887
Arranged like this.

245
00:14:48.017 --> 00:14:50.497
They were on the porch
on the side of the house.

246
00:14:50.628 --> 00:14:52.758
Huh.

247
00:14:52.892 --> 00:14:56.292
Well. it seems we have a phantom
florist running around.

248
00:14:56.417 --> 00:14:57.637
Come on. It's laundry day.

249
00:14:57.766 --> 00:14:59.116
[Gasps]

250
00:14:59.246 --> 00:15:01.066
[Laughs]
Come on.

251
00:15:05.600 --> 00:15:06.690
[Jade] Ow!

252
00:15:06.818 --> 00:15:09.298
Motherfucker! Come on!

253
00:15:09.430 --> 00:15:10.260
Ugh.

254
00:15:12.912 --> 00:15:14.832
These people are ding-dongs.
They stripped the car.

255
00:15:14.957 --> 00:15:17.127
They leave behind the only
parts that actually matter.

256
00:15:17.264 --> 00:15:18.224
They're not all ding-dongs.

257
00:15:18.352 --> 00:15:19.182
Battery's gone.

258
00:15:19.309 --> 00:15:20.659
Huh?

259
00:15:20.789 --> 00:15:22.359
I said.
the battery is gone.

260
00:15:24.793 --> 00:15:26.713
That means we gotta
go back to town.

261
00:15:26.838 --> 00:15:29.488
Wait. just as soon
as I get this cable here.

262
00:15:29.624 --> 00:15:30.804
Goddamn it. come on.

263
00:15:30.930 --> 00:15:34.410
Why all the way out here?

264
00:15:34.542 --> 00:15:37.762
We literally could've gotten
wiring from any car in town.

265
00:15:37.893 --> 00:15:41.723
My friend. this is
a top-of-the-line Audi Q5.

266
00:15:41.853 --> 00:15:44.033
Parts sourced from--

267
00:15:44.160 --> 00:15:46.600
You really wanna pin our hopes
to some peasant model jalopy?

268
00:15:47.859 --> 00:15:48.689
Yep.

269
00:15:50.297 --> 00:15:51.167
You got all that?

270
00:15:54.344 --> 00:15:56.224
Whoo!
We're doing it!

271
00:15:56.346 --> 00:15:57.386
Science!

272
00:16:08.793 --> 00:16:11.273
[Sighing]
Good morning.

273
00:16:11.405 --> 00:16:13.095
Uh. I'm dropping
these off for storage.

274
00:16:26.159 --> 00:16:27.939
Hey.

275
00:16:28.074 --> 00:16:31.124
Honey. she's not here.
She's not gonna hurt you.

276
00:16:31.251 --> 00:16:32.731
Promise?

277
00:16:32.861 --> 00:16:34.341
Yeah. I promise.

278
00:16:38.649 --> 00:16:40.479
Come on.

279
00:16:45.656 --> 00:16:46.656
Where should I...?

280
00:16:46.788 --> 00:16:48.398
[Door opening]

281
00:16:48.529 --> 00:16:51.139
Wow.
Look at all this stuff.

282
00:16:58.756 --> 00:17:00.186
Hey.

283
00:17:00.323 --> 00:17:01.633
Don't touch anything.

284
00:17:01.759 --> 00:17:03.719
Why?

285
00:17:03.848 --> 00:17:06.548
Because this-- this used to
belong to other people.

286
00:17:06.677 --> 00:17:08.107
The people
who lived here?

287
00:17:08.244 --> 00:17:09.164
Mm-hmm.

288
00:17:09.289 --> 00:17:10.509
Oh.

289
00:17:12.379 --> 00:17:15.469
It's like the cavern
of the lonely dragon.

290
00:17:15.599 --> 00:17:17.299
Yeah?

291
00:17:17.427 --> 00:17:20.337
When the Cromenockle was
lost in the rainbow sky.

292
00:17:20.474 --> 00:17:23.614
she found a cavern where
the lonely dragon lived.

293
00:17:23.738 --> 00:17:27.258
and it was full of stuff
that nobody wanted.

294
00:17:27.394 --> 00:17:31.444
But for the lonely dragon.

295
00:17:31.572 --> 00:17:33.492
all the stuff was treasure.
And guess what.

296
00:17:33.617 --> 00:17:34.917
What?

297
00:17:35.054 --> 00:17:37.624
In one of the
big piles of stuff.

298
00:17:37.752 --> 00:17:41.022
there was the map
of the rainbow sky.

299
00:17:41.147 --> 00:17:44.847
So. the lonely dragon
gave it to the Cromenockle

300
00:17:44.976 --> 00:17:46.666
and then she
wasn't lost anymore.

301
00:17:46.804 --> 00:17:49.374
So maybe we'll
find a map in here.

302
00:17:49.503 --> 00:17:52.333
Yeah. maybe we will.

303
00:18:01.254 --> 00:18:02.784
Mom?

304
00:18:02.907 --> 00:18:04.557
Yeah.

305
00:18:04.692 --> 00:18:06.482
What's wrong?

306
00:18:08.957 --> 00:18:11.217
Nothing.

307
00:18:15.224 --> 00:18:18.754
[Jade] Yeah. this is it.
this one. right here.

308
00:18:23.928 --> 00:18:25.368
Oh. this'll
never work.

309
00:18:25.495 --> 00:18:26.885
Of course.
it's going to work.

310
00:18:27.018 --> 00:18:30.278
No. it's not
nearly tall enough.

311
00:18:30.413 --> 00:18:31.813
It won't have
the signal strength.

312
00:18:31.936 --> 00:18:33.626
Yeah. listen. we can
deal with that. okay?

313
00:18:33.764 --> 00:18:36.294
This is just a test run.
Look. you're an engineer. right?

314
00:18:36.419 --> 00:18:37.729
Amusement parks?

315
00:18:37.855 --> 00:18:39.505
Yeah.

316
00:18:39.640 --> 00:18:41.560
Okay. So. I guess that
means one of us built

317
00:18:41.685 --> 00:18:43.505
a multi-million-dollar
software company

318
00:18:43.644 --> 00:18:46.524
and the other does. what.
safety tests on the teacup ride?

319
00:18:49.476 --> 00:18:52.696
You know what?
Do it yourself.

320
00:18:52.827 --> 00:18:55.347
Huh? Wait. no. no! Hey. look.
I'm sorry. okay? I'm sorry.

321
00:18:55.482 --> 00:18:57.312
People tell me I'm not great
when it comes to

322
00:18:57.440 --> 00:18:58.490
talking to people.

323
00:18:58.615 --> 00:18:59.745
You have no idea
what it's like

324
00:18:59.877 --> 00:19:01.397
being smarter
than everyone you know.

325
00:19:01.531 --> 00:19:03.881
Listen. okay. look.
the truth is...

326
00:19:04.012 --> 00:19:05.802
I could really
use your help.

327
00:19:05.927 --> 00:19:08.927
Yeah. you could.

328
00:19:09.060 --> 00:19:12.590
This antenna.
it has to go up high.

329
00:19:12.716 --> 00:19:15.366
That is the highest tree that I
could find. but I-- I can't.

330
00:19:15.502 --> 00:19:17.902
[Stammers] I get vertigo.

331
00:19:19.070 --> 00:19:20.810
So. you brought me
out here to climb a tree?

332
00:19:23.945 --> 00:19:24.895
Yeah.

333
00:19:25.033 --> 00:19:26.433
[Scoffs]

334
00:19:26.556 --> 00:19:27.856
Listen.
you don't like me.

335
00:19:27.992 --> 00:19:29.172
All right? That's fine.

336
00:19:31.866 --> 00:19:33.906
But if there's even
the slightest chance

337
00:19:34.042 --> 00:19:37.922
this could work.
don't you want to know for sure?

338
00:19:40.831 --> 00:19:44.181
Yeah. Yeah. I do.

339
00:19:46.750 --> 00:19:49.280
Okay.

340
00:19:49.405 --> 00:19:50.665
All right.

341
00:19:57.239 --> 00:19:59.679
All right.
Pass me up the cable?

342
00:20:00.938 --> 00:20:05.678
[Birds chirping]

343
00:20:19.566 --> 00:20:21.866
Kristi. you here?

344
00:20:33.493 --> 00:20:43.373
♪

345
00:21:04.567 --> 00:21:06.657
[Kristi] Sheriff Boyd?

346
00:21:06.787 --> 00:21:09.917
Kristi. hey.

347
00:21:10.051 --> 00:21:11.711
I-I was just. uh...

348
00:21:11.835 --> 00:21:12.835
I didn't see
you upstairs. so...

349
00:21:12.967 --> 00:21:15.577
Everything okay?

350
00:21:15.709 --> 00:21:18.579
I know you and Kenny are close.
and I was just. uh...

351
00:21:18.712 --> 00:21:20.932
How's he doing?

352
00:21:21.062 --> 00:21:23.892
Well. I mean...

353
00:21:24.021 --> 00:21:27.631
I think he's...
been having a hard time since...

354
00:21:27.764 --> 00:21:29.684
Right. right.

355
00:21:29.810 --> 00:21:31.730
And I-I think he's
trying really hard

356
00:21:31.855 --> 00:21:33.635
to be this person that he
thinks people need him to be.

357
00:21:33.770 --> 00:21:35.560
if that makes sense?

358
00:21:35.685 --> 00:21:37.115
Yeah.

359
00:21:37.252 --> 00:21:39.862
Being your deputy and...

360
00:21:39.994 --> 00:21:42.564
and I know
a big thing for him

361
00:21:42.692 --> 00:21:44.612
is he doesn't want
to let you down.

362
00:21:44.738 --> 00:21:48.128
I know. And I'm really trying
not to push him too hard.

363
00:21:48.263 --> 00:21:50.003
The truth is. he needs
to be ready to lead.

364
00:21:50.134 --> 00:21:51.534
Can I be honest
with you?

365
00:21:51.658 --> 00:21:53.788
Please.

366
00:21:53.921 --> 00:21:56.011
I get that you want to
prepare him for the worst.

367
00:21:56.140 --> 00:21:59.010
get him ready to take your
place in case something ever...

368
00:22:01.145 --> 00:22:03.575
But right now.
he's really hurting.

369
00:22:03.713 --> 00:22:05.633
and I don't think
he needs a sheriff.

370
00:22:05.759 --> 00:22:08.329
I think he needs a dad.

371
00:22:10.067 --> 00:22:12.507
Goddamn it.

372
00:22:12.635 --> 00:22:13.935
I'm sorry. I...

373
00:22:14.071 --> 00:22:15.251
No. no. no.

374
00:22:15.377 --> 00:22:17.637
It's...
It's not you. It's me.

375
00:22:17.771 --> 00:22:19.951
It's...
[Sighs]

376
00:22:20.077 --> 00:22:21.777
If you don't learn
from your mistakes.

377
00:22:21.905 --> 00:22:23.245
you're doomed to
repeat them. right?

378
00:22:23.385 --> 00:22:26.815
[Kristi]
I really didn't mean to...

379
00:22:26.954 --> 00:22:28.564
[Boyd] You didn't.
[Stammers] No apology.

380
00:22:32.002 --> 00:22:33.702
Thank you. Kristi.

381
00:22:43.753 --> 00:22:53.683
♪

382
00:22:56.244 --> 00:23:00.204
People think the
Bible's a fixed object -

383
00:23:00.335 --> 00:23:02.685
something written.
completed.

384
00:23:04.426 --> 00:23:05.986
But how can
the story be finished

385
00:23:06.123 --> 00:23:09.913
if all the players
remain on stage?

386
00:23:10.040 --> 00:23:11.780
We call it
"the Good Book". but...

387
00:23:14.523 --> 00:23:18.573
Did you know it's actually
comprised of 73 books?

388
00:23:18.701 --> 00:23:19.531
Did you know that?

389
00:23:22.357 --> 00:23:25.747
Matthew. Mark.

390
00:23:25.882 --> 00:23:27.932
Romans. Corinthians.

391
00:23:28.058 --> 00:23:29.798
Seventy-three books.

392
00:23:31.148 --> 00:23:34.888
All filled with tales
of miracle and wonder.

393
00:23:40.157 --> 00:23:43.637
But there's also
darkness in the Bible.

394
00:23:43.770 --> 00:23:46.640
Gruesome. horrible things.

395
00:23:46.773 --> 00:23:48.563
You know. since--

396
00:23:48.688 --> 00:23:52.738
since the night I arrived.

397
00:23:52.866 --> 00:23:55.996
there seems to be a question
I keep coming back to.

398
00:24:01.875 --> 00:24:04.565
Seventy-three books.

399
00:24:05.835 --> 00:24:08.615
What if we.

400
00:24:08.751 --> 00:24:12.451
the people of this town.

401
00:24:12.581 --> 00:24:15.541
are living the book
that has yet to be written?

402
00:24:16.803 --> 00:24:19.683
What if this is Book 74?

403
00:24:22.983 --> 00:24:27.553
And. Sara.
what if we were chosen?

404
00:24:28.945 --> 00:24:30.595
For what?

405
00:24:33.950 --> 00:24:36.080
I don't know.

406
00:24:39.956 --> 00:24:42.826
Which is why I need you to
tell me about these voices.

407
00:24:48.225 --> 00:24:49.615
Please.

408
00:24:56.886 --> 00:24:59.496
[Ethan]
When's Dad coming home?

409
00:25:00.977 --> 00:25:02.457
[Exhales]
Soon. honey.

410
00:25:02.588 --> 00:25:04.848
I don't think
he will be much longer.

411
00:25:07.288 --> 00:25:08.588
What's wrong?

412
00:25:10.944 --> 00:25:13.864
Nothing. I'm just--

413
00:25:13.990 --> 00:25:16.650
just admiring this piece
of lonely dragon's treasure.

414
00:25:16.776 --> 00:25:18.646
It's pretty.

415
00:25:20.040 --> 00:25:21.610
Yeah.

416
00:25:24.261 --> 00:25:27.181
Why does that light
keep turning off?

417
00:25:30.964 --> 00:25:32.664
I don't know.

418
00:25:33.793 --> 00:25:36.753
How about you
and I have an adventure?

419
00:25:36.883 --> 00:25:38.713
What kind of adventure?

420
00:25:38.841 --> 00:25:41.981
Mm. some sort of.
um. treasure hunt.

421
00:25:42.105 --> 00:25:43.665
Really?

422
00:25:43.803 --> 00:25:44.983
Mm-hmm.

423
00:25:45.108 --> 00:25:46.888
Yeah. the game's
gonna be called.

424
00:25:47.023 --> 00:25:49.683
"Where does
the light come from?"

425
00:25:49.809 --> 00:25:51.419
Sounds good?

426
00:25:51.550 --> 00:25:53.860
-Yeah.
-Let's do it.

427
00:25:53.987 --> 00:25:57.687
Let's go. Okay.
we will need some tools. right?

428
00:25:57.817 --> 00:25:58.687
Mm-hmm.

429
00:25:58.818 --> 00:26:01.598
Ooh. I found your tool!

430
00:26:02.822 --> 00:26:05.912
Let's see if I've...

431
00:26:06.042 --> 00:26:07.352
found my tool.

432
00:26:08.828 --> 00:26:11.048
Okay.

433
00:26:13.876 --> 00:26:15.226
Let's move this.

434
00:26:15.356 --> 00:26:18.616
Come on. honey.
I need you to push. Help me.

435
00:26:23.843 --> 00:26:25.893
Okeydokey.

436
00:26:26.019 --> 00:26:27.759
Now. this is your tool.

437
00:26:27.890 --> 00:26:30.280
This is my tool. Ready?

438
00:26:31.981 --> 00:26:32.681
[Ethan] Mom!

439
00:26:35.202 --> 00:26:37.602
You're doin' great!

440
00:26:44.167 --> 00:26:45.947
Here we go.

441
00:26:53.133 --> 00:26:54.963
Hey. I'm snagged somewhere.
Can you see where it's caught?

442
00:26:55.091 --> 00:26:57.661
Uh. no. not really.

443
00:26:57.790 --> 00:26:59.620
Just. uh. give it a shake.
see if you can wiggle it free.

444
00:27:03.230 --> 00:27:04.840
Yeah. that's it.

445
00:27:04.971 --> 00:27:07.101
-[Jade] You got it?
-Yup.

446
00:27:13.196 --> 00:27:15.066
All right.

447
00:27:15.198 --> 00:27:17.718
Okay.
How you doing up there?

448
00:27:17.853 --> 00:27:19.773
[Jim] Doing good.

449
00:27:20.813 --> 00:27:22.643
Fuck!

450
00:27:24.033 --> 00:27:25.823
Oh. Jesus.

451
00:27:25.948 --> 00:27:26.778
[Breathing heavily]

452
00:27:30.257 --> 00:27:33.217
[Gasps in horror]

453
00:27:33.347 --> 00:27:37.697
[Breathing heavily]

454
00:27:52.279 --> 00:27:53.929
No. no. no! No!

455
00:27:54.063 --> 00:27:55.023
-[Gunshot]
-[Screaming]

456
00:27:58.372 --> 00:28:00.812
[Screaming indistinctly]

457
00:28:00.940 --> 00:28:04.680
[Screaming]

458
00:28:08.948 --> 00:28:09.778
[Screams]

459
00:28:14.301 --> 00:28:15.821
No. no. no! No. no!

460
00:28:15.955 --> 00:28:17.995
[Groans]

461
00:28:18.131 --> 00:28:20.221
[Gasping for breath]

462
00:28:20.350 --> 00:28:22.050
No. no!

463
00:28:22.178 --> 00:28:23.788
[Gasping for breath]

464
00:28:23.919 --> 00:28:27.969
[Jim] Hey. Hey.

465
00:28:28.097 --> 00:28:29.967
Jade. wh--

466
00:28:30.099 --> 00:28:32.969
Jade. Jade. right here.
Right here.

467
00:28:33.102 --> 00:28:35.372
Listen. whatever it is.
it's not real. Okay?

468
00:28:35.496 --> 00:28:38.146
There's nothing there.

469
00:28:38.281 --> 00:28:40.021
Jade. I'm going
to help you up.

470
00:28:40.153 --> 00:28:41.813
Come here.
Come here.

471
00:28:41.937 --> 00:28:43.977
You okay? Huh?

472
00:28:44.113 --> 00:28:45.333
Just get your
fucking hands off me!

473
00:28:45.462 --> 00:28:46.942
What did you see?

474
00:28:47.073 --> 00:28:48.903
Just fuck off. all right?

475
00:28:54.254 --> 00:28:57.084
They said they wanted to help.

476
00:28:57.213 --> 00:28:59.393
That they'd been here
a long time

477
00:28:59.520 --> 00:29:01.040
and they'd been waiting

478
00:29:01.174 --> 00:29:03.964
for someone to come
who would hear them.

479
00:29:04.090 --> 00:29:05.920
someone who could help them.

480
00:29:06.048 --> 00:29:07.218
Help them do what?

481
00:29:07.354 --> 00:29:09.364
Help them escape.

482
00:29:09.486 --> 00:29:11.526
Help them go home.

483
00:29:11.662 --> 00:29:14.362
They said they were
just like us.

484
00:29:14.491 --> 00:29:19.021
But why?
Why did you believe them?

485
00:29:19.148 --> 00:29:23.068
Because...
they told me things.

486
00:29:23.196 --> 00:29:26.496
things they couldn't know.

487
00:29:26.634 --> 00:29:30.124
They told me those
two cars were coming

488
00:29:30.246 --> 00:29:33.896
and to stand out near the edge
of town and I would see.

489
00:29:34.598 --> 00:29:36.948
They said it happened before.

490
00:29:37.079 --> 00:29:41.169
that two cars came
on the same day

491
00:29:41.301 --> 00:29:44.351
and everyone died.

492
00:29:44.478 --> 00:29:46.998
They said it was because of the
people in the cars. but if...

493
00:29:50.136 --> 00:29:53.396
...if I did what they said.

494
00:29:53.530 --> 00:29:57.230
that we'd be safe.
we'd get to go home.

495
00:29:59.101 --> 00:30:01.361
Okay. How?

496
00:30:01.495 --> 00:30:06.105
How would we get to go home?

497
00:30:10.504 --> 00:30:12.724
-I don't know.
-Okay.

498
00:30:12.854 --> 00:30:16.644
Do you still believe that
they were telling the truth?

499
00:30:16.771 --> 00:30:20.991
They promised...
that Nathan would be okay.

500
00:30:23.212 --> 00:30:26.222
They-they promised.
and now. now he's...

501
00:30:26.346 --> 00:30:29.176
[Screaming]

502
00:30:29.305 --> 00:30:30.565
-Sara.
-[Screaming]

503
00:30:30.698 --> 00:30:32.048
Sara. listen to me.
Come here.

504
00:30:32.178 --> 00:30:34.218
Listen to me.
Listen to me. Sara.

505
00:30:34.354 --> 00:30:36.444
If these voices are real.

506
00:30:36.573 --> 00:30:38.533
if something here is
communicating with you.

507
00:30:38.662 --> 00:30:40.452
then that means you're
connected to this place

508
00:30:40.577 --> 00:30:42.097
in a way that
no one else here is.

509
00:30:42.231 --> 00:30:44.361
and that makes you
incredibly valuable.

510
00:30:44.494 --> 00:30:45.544
Do you understand?

511
00:30:45.669 --> 00:30:47.629
But we need proof.

512
00:30:47.758 --> 00:30:51.278
We need to be able
to go to Sheriff Boyd

513
00:30:51.414 --> 00:30:54.164
and tell him with absolute
certainty that you--

514
00:30:54.287 --> 00:30:55.507
That I'm not crazy.

515
00:30:55.636 --> 00:30:58.196
No. the voices.
that these voices are not simply

516
00:30:58.334 --> 00:31:00.124
the product of a troubled mind.

517
00:31:00.249 --> 00:31:02.249
So. Sara. I need--

518
00:31:02.382 --> 00:31:03.342
Ow!

519
00:31:03.470 --> 00:31:04.510
-Sara?
-Ow.

520
00:31:04.645 --> 00:31:06.465
-What?
-Ow. No!

521
00:31:06.603 --> 00:31:08.693
-What?
-[Screams]

522
00:31:08.823 --> 00:31:10.693
-Sara.
-No! No!

523
00:31:10.825 --> 00:31:12.695
-What?
-No. no. no!

524
00:31:12.827 --> 00:31:15.397
-What?
-Please! Ah. no. no!

525
00:31:15.525 --> 00:31:17.475
-What?
-[Screams]

526
00:31:17.614 --> 00:31:19.054
-Sara. what is it?
-Ah. no!

527
00:31:19.181 --> 00:31:20.141
What?

528
00:31:20.269 --> 00:31:22.319
I need-- I need...

529
00:31:22.445 --> 00:31:23.315
Need what?

530
00:31:23.446 --> 00:31:24.576
Paper.

531
00:31:24.708 --> 00:31:26.318
Paper.

532
00:31:26.449 --> 00:31:28.189
[Gasping]

533
00:31:30.845 --> 00:31:33.365
They want me to
show you something.

534
00:31:33.500 --> 00:31:38.290
[Birds chirping]

535
00:31:56.262 --> 00:31:58.262
[Static buzzing lightly]

536
00:31:58.394 --> 00:31:59.664
[Static buzzing]

537
00:32:01.354 --> 00:32:02.274
[Static buzzing loudly]

538
00:32:02.398 --> 00:32:07.228
[Static buzzing]

539
00:32:11.277 --> 00:32:14.237
Hello?
Is anybody out there?

540
00:32:14.367 --> 00:32:16.407
[Static buzzing lightly]

541
00:32:18.371 --> 00:32:20.591
-Hello?
-[Static buzzing lightly]

542
00:32:22.853 --> 00:32:24.073
Is anybody there?

543
00:32:37.259 --> 00:32:38.349
[Grunts]

544
00:32:41.785 --> 00:32:43.435
[Speaks Cantonese]

545
00:32:43.570 --> 00:32:46.090
I don't want any tea!

546
00:32:47.530 --> 00:32:50.450
[Speaks Cantonese]

547
00:32:52.405 --> 00:32:54.535
You realize I have no
idea what you're saying.

548
00:32:57.279 --> 00:32:58.629
Fine.

549
00:33:06.854 --> 00:33:08.334
It's good.

550
00:33:08.464 --> 00:33:09.994
Thanks.

551
00:33:16.864 --> 00:33:19.394
I keep seeing it.
I-I keep--

552
00:33:19.519 --> 00:33:21.129
[Stammers. sighing]

553
00:33:21.260 --> 00:33:23.610
I keep having these. uh...

554
00:33:23.740 --> 00:33:25.090
[Exhales]

555
00:33:27.962 --> 00:33:30.312
Hey. where are you going?

556
00:33:33.924 --> 00:33:35.404
Hello?

557
00:33:36.623 --> 00:33:37.753
Where'd you go?

558
00:33:47.895 --> 00:33:50.675
Holy shit.

559
00:33:50.811 --> 00:33:53.251
This is all the. uh...

560
00:33:53.379 --> 00:33:55.639
Wow. Oh. wait. wait!
Hold on.

561
00:33:55.772 --> 00:33:57.382
Slow down. Tian.
I got this.

562
00:34:00.342 --> 00:34:03.352
[Exhales]

563
00:34:03.476 --> 00:34:05.256
What--

564
00:34:05.391 --> 00:34:07.181
what are you looking for?

565
00:34:09.656 --> 00:34:11.266
[Clattering]

566
00:34:11.397 --> 00:34:13.437
What is that?
It's a yearbook.

567
00:34:13.573 --> 00:34:15.713
1972?
How many people...?

568
00:34:17.533 --> 00:34:19.623
[Speaks Cantonese]

569
00:34:19.753 --> 00:34:21.893
Okay.

570
00:34:22.016 --> 00:34:24.666
Well. I mean. could you tell me
what you're looking for?

571
00:34:24.801 --> 00:34:26.671
Shh.

572
00:34:29.806 --> 00:34:31.156
What's that?

573
00:34:35.638 --> 00:34:36.768
Hmm?

574
00:34:48.216 --> 00:34:54.046
♪

575
00:34:54.179 --> 00:34:58.309
[Breathing rapidly]
Oh. what the fuck?

576
00:34:58.444 --> 00:35:02.884
[Sara gasping. whimpering]

577
00:35:07.366 --> 00:35:11.666
[Whimpering]

578
00:35:11.805 --> 00:35:12.755
Please...

579
00:35:12.893 --> 00:35:14.903
I can't...

580
00:35:15.025 --> 00:35:19.245
[Breathing heavily]

581
00:35:19.378 --> 00:35:21.818
[Gasps]

582
00:35:21.945 --> 00:35:25.465
[Breathing heavily]

583
00:35:28.038 --> 00:35:31.388
[Breathing heavily]

584
00:35:34.871 --> 00:35:38.221
I don't...

585
00:35:38.353 --> 00:35:40.573
What is this?

586
00:35:40.703 --> 00:35:43.103
They said...

587
00:35:43.228 --> 00:35:47.748
They said they watched you
on the day you got here.

588
00:35:47.884 --> 00:35:51.454
They said they
watched you bury the bag

589
00:35:51.584 --> 00:35:53.804
and that this is proof
that they're real.

590
00:35:59.026 --> 00:36:00.716
Do you know what that means?

591
00:36:00.854 --> 00:36:02.944
[inhales deeply]

592
00:36:18.872 --> 00:36:19.832
Oh!

593
00:36:25.052 --> 00:36:26.492
Ah! Here we go.

594
00:36:27.750 --> 00:36:28.580
Okay.

595
00:36:30.623 --> 00:36:32.023
Yeah.

596
00:36:32.146 --> 00:36:35.846
That's it.
There we go.

597
00:36:38.370 --> 00:36:39.330
Hey.

598
00:36:39.458 --> 00:36:40.678
Sheriff Boyd.

599
00:36:43.940 --> 00:36:44.940
Ladies.

600
00:36:45.072 --> 00:36:46.602
Hi!

601
00:36:46.726 --> 00:36:49.206
[Chattering]

602
00:36:51.470 --> 00:36:52.650
Fuck!

603
00:36:54.473 --> 00:36:55.823
[Knocking]

604
00:36:55.952 --> 00:36:57.002
Come in.

605
00:36:57.127 --> 00:36:58.477
[Door opening]

606
00:36:58.607 --> 00:36:59.647
[Boyd] Hey.

607
00:36:59.782 --> 00:37:01.222
[Door closing]

608
00:37:06.224 --> 00:37:10.234
I was. uh. going through my
things back at the station.

609
00:37:10.358 --> 00:37:13.668
and I realized I haven't thrown
a ball around in a while.

610
00:37:13.796 --> 00:37:15.486
Come on outside.

611
00:37:15.624 --> 00:37:17.414
You can help an old man
knock the rust off.

612
00:37:17.539 --> 00:37:19.369
I'm good.

613
00:37:22.936 --> 00:37:25.416
Hey. I ever tell
you. uh.

614
00:37:25.547 --> 00:37:27.677
I played first base
back in college.

615
00:37:27.810 --> 00:37:29.510
No.

616
00:37:29.638 --> 00:37:31.158
Yeah. I was
pretty good too.

617
00:37:31.292 --> 00:37:33.992
Had a couple scouts
kicking around.

618
00:37:34.121 --> 00:37:36.821
Here I am.
18 years old. thinkin'.

619
00:37:36.950 --> 00:37:39.820
"Man. I might
be going to the show.

620
00:37:39.953 --> 00:37:43.043
"be the next Willie McCovey."

621
00:37:43.173 --> 00:37:44.963
What happened?

622
00:37:47.569 --> 00:37:51.439
Oh. you know...

623
00:37:51.573 --> 00:37:53.363
life had other plans.

624
00:37:57.013 --> 00:37:59.673
Life always seems
to have other plans.

625
00:38:07.981 --> 00:38:09.291
I'm sick. Kenny.

626
00:38:13.682 --> 00:38:15.122
What do you...?

627
00:38:15.249 --> 00:38:17.469
Have you talked
to Kristi about it?

628
00:38:17.599 --> 00:38:20.599
Not that kind of sick.

629
00:38:20.733 --> 00:38:22.913
My father was diagnosed
with Parkinson's

630
00:38:23.039 --> 00:38:24.649
when he was around my age.

631
00:38:24.780 --> 00:38:27.130
It's not supposed
to be hereditary.

632
00:38:27.261 --> 00:38:28.521
The doctors all
swore up and down

633
00:38:28.654 --> 00:38:31.574
how extremely rare
that would be.

634
00:38:31.700 --> 00:38:34.620
Wrong time to win
the lottery. I guess.

635
00:38:34.747 --> 00:38:39.057
But how do you know that...?
How do you know?

636
00:38:39.186 --> 00:38:40.486
I mean.
it could be anything. right?

637
00:38:40.622 --> 00:38:41.882
It is what it is.

638
00:38:44.147 --> 00:38:47.237
Look...

639
00:38:47.368 --> 00:38:50.108
this thing is already
chipping away at me.

640
00:38:51.546 --> 00:38:54.676
And eventually. I'm gonna get
to the point where I can't--

641
00:38:54.810 --> 00:38:59.770
I'm not gonna be able to protect
these people anymore.

642
00:38:59.902 --> 00:39:03.992
So I gotta find us a way out
while I still can.

643
00:39:04.124 --> 00:39:06.564
You understand?

644
00:39:06.692 --> 00:39:09.352
The only way
I can do this

645
00:39:09.477 --> 00:39:11.437
is because I know these people
are gonna be in good hands

646
00:39:11.566 --> 00:39:13.086
when I'm gone.

647
00:39:15.701 --> 00:39:17.571
There's a lot of folks
in this town

648
00:39:17.703 --> 00:39:21.793
who are alive today
because of you.

649
00:39:21.924 --> 00:39:24.884
And I know your dad
isn't around to say it.

650
00:39:25.014 --> 00:39:27.634
but I promise you...

651
00:39:27.756 --> 00:39:29.886
he's so goddamn proud of you.

652
00:39:31.238 --> 00:39:33.068
I'm proud of you.

653
00:39:33.196 --> 00:39:36.586
But if you tell me
right now

654
00:39:36.722 --> 00:39:39.032
that you are not ready
for me to go.

655
00:39:39.159 --> 00:39:43.209
that you need more time.

656
00:39:43.337 --> 00:39:45.507
then I ain't
going nowhere.

657
00:39:45.644 --> 00:39:48.044
Okay?

658
00:39:48.168 --> 00:39:50.038
[Exhales]

659
00:40:01.268 --> 00:40:03.748
[Scoffs]

660
00:40:03.879 --> 00:40:06.059
Well. we doing
this or what?

661
00:40:07.709 --> 00:40:09.539
Doing it.

662
00:40:13.193 --> 00:40:17.423
Hey? Anybody here?

663
00:40:17.545 --> 00:40:20.895
We might be onto something
with this radio.

664
00:40:21.027 --> 00:40:22.677
We're gonna have to get it
higher up. but it could...

665
00:40:26.728 --> 00:40:27.818
What the fuck?

666
00:40:27.947 --> 00:40:30.727
[Footsteps approaching]

667
00:40:30.863 --> 00:40:32.693
[Grunting]
Hi. Dad.

668
00:40:32.821 --> 00:40:34.001
Hey. kiddo.

669
00:40:34.127 --> 00:40:35.257
What you up to?

670
00:40:35.389 --> 00:40:36.609
We're on an adventure.

671
00:40:36.738 --> 00:40:38.258
There's a lot of dirt.

672
00:40:38.392 --> 00:40:40.662
so mom said I should
bring some outside.

673
00:40:40.786 --> 00:40:42.136
Uh-huh.
And where is your mother?

674
00:40:42.265 --> 00:40:43.475
[Ethan]
In the basement.

675
00:40:44.746 --> 00:40:49.186
[Clattering]

676
00:40:50.926 --> 00:40:55.236
[Clattering]

677
00:40:55.365 --> 00:41:00.105
[Shovel clattering]

678
00:41:00.240 --> 00:41:04.460
[Clattering]

679
00:41:06.768 --> 00:41:08.158
Tabitha?

680
00:41:08.291 --> 00:41:11.601
Hey. Hey.
How'd things go?

681
00:41:11.730 --> 00:41:12.860
Good.

682
00:41:12.992 --> 00:41:14.172
Yeah?

683
00:41:14.297 --> 00:41:15.907
We got some static. so...

684
00:41:16.038 --> 00:41:17.778
Yeah. well.
that's wonderful. right?

685
00:41:17.910 --> 00:41:19.610
Yeah. it's a start.

686
00:41:19.738 --> 00:41:21.388
What you doing?

687
00:41:21.522 --> 00:41:23.312
It's like you
said this morning.

688
00:41:23.437 --> 00:41:26.787
it has to come from somewhere.
right? The electricity.

689
00:41:26.919 --> 00:41:30.229
There's no power lines.
and all the wires.

690
00:41:30.357 --> 00:41:31.967
all the cords. they just...

691
00:41:32.098 --> 00:41:34.928
they just go down.
straight down.

692
00:41:35.057 --> 00:41:38.667
It's so weird.

693
00:41:38.800 --> 00:41:41.670
Okay. Uh. sorry. can you...

694
00:41:41.803 --> 00:41:43.593
not dig for a moment?

695
00:41:43.718 --> 00:41:44.628
Yes.

696
00:41:47.374 --> 00:41:48.774
What's going on?

697
00:41:48.897 --> 00:41:51.547
[Sighing]
Okay.

698
00:41:53.902 --> 00:41:56.122
Do you remember
the bracelet I made you?

699
00:41:57.689 --> 00:41:59.519
The what?

700
00:41:59.647 --> 00:42:01.907
The bracelet I made you
after our first few dates.

701
00:42:02.041 --> 00:42:03.781
from. uh. the laces of
your father's boots.

702
00:42:03.912 --> 00:42:05.352
Yeah. of course. I remember.

703
00:42:05.479 --> 00:42:06.739
Okay. Remember.

704
00:42:06.872 --> 00:42:09.662
you lost it at the hospital
the night Julie was born.

705
00:42:09.788 --> 00:42:11.748
Okay.

706
00:42:11.877 --> 00:42:14.577
Turn around.
Look what's sitting there.

707
00:42:20.712 --> 00:42:21.842
[Scoffs]

708
00:42:28.197 --> 00:42:29.937
Okay. I still don't get it.

709
00:42:30.069 --> 00:42:31.769
You're saying
you found a bracelet

710
00:42:31.897 --> 00:42:33.117
that's similar to
the one you gave--

711
00:42:33.246 --> 00:42:34.936
No. no. no. no.
It's not similar.

712
00:42:35.074 --> 00:42:36.734
That is the bracelet.
Those are the laces

713
00:42:36.858 --> 00:42:37.768
from your father's boots!

714
00:42:37.903 --> 00:42:39.773
No. those were generic
rawhide laces.

715
00:42:39.905 --> 00:42:41.945
the same you'd find on any boot.

716
00:42:42.081 --> 00:42:44.911
No. no. no. no. no. no.
Look. Look at this.

717
00:42:45.040 --> 00:42:45.910
Look at this.

718
00:42:46.041 --> 00:42:47.521
What?

719
00:42:47.652 --> 00:42:50.262
This was an accident.
I made this.

720
00:42:50.393 --> 00:42:52.963
I was so afraid I ruined it.
but then. when I gave it to you.

721
00:42:53.092 --> 00:42:54.092
you said. "Accidents--"

722
00:42:54.223 --> 00:42:55.663
"Accidents are the best part."

723
00:42:55.790 --> 00:42:57.530
Yes. Why?

724
00:42:57.662 --> 00:42:59.012
Ah. because it makes
it one of a kind.

725
00:42:59.141 --> 00:43:00.621
Exactly.

726
00:43:05.887 --> 00:43:08.017
It's impossible.

727
00:43:08.150 --> 00:43:10.280
Jim. everything
about this is impossible.

728
00:43:10.413 --> 00:43:11.813
That doesn't
make any sense.

729
00:43:11.937 --> 00:43:14.587
Those wires
don't make sense.

730
00:43:14.722 --> 00:43:17.072
We may not be able to
find out how this got here.

731
00:43:17.203 --> 00:43:19.903
but we can find out
where those wires go.

732
00:43:23.209 --> 00:43:24.729
Give me the shovel.

733
00:43:30.216 --> 00:43:33.866
[Breathing heavily]

734
00:43:34.002 --> 00:43:36.882
[Grunting]

735
00:43:41.140 --> 00:43:45.750
[Breathing heavily]

736
00:43:50.105 --> 00:44:00.025
♪

737
00:44:36.282 --> 00:44:40.982
[indistinct chatter]

738
00:44:43.637 --> 00:44:45.157
Where's yours?

739
00:44:45.291 --> 00:44:46.471
First base.
I don't need no glove.

740
00:44:46.596 --> 00:44:48.416
[Laughs]

741
00:44:48.555 --> 00:44:50.245
Are you sure?
Because I got some heat.

742
00:44:50.383 --> 00:44:52.213
Just throw the damn ball.

743
00:44:52.341 --> 00:44:54.301
You're gonna regret this.

744
00:44:54.430 --> 00:44:56.820
I hear a lot of talking.
but I'm not--

745
00:44:56.955 --> 00:44:57.345
Here comes the heat.

746
00:45:02.221 --> 00:45:07.051
I think. uh--
think maybe I'll carve us a bat.

747
00:45:07.182 --> 00:45:11.102
That way. when you get back.
we can do this right.

748
00:45:11.230 --> 00:45:13.360
When I get back. huh?

749
00:45:14.668 --> 00:45:16.838
Yeah. when you get back.

750
00:45:16.975 --> 00:45:26.845
♪

751
00:45:28.290 --> 00:45:29.860
Yeah.

752
00:45:36.342 --> 00:45:41.092
[Quiet snoring]

753
00:45:48.006 --> 00:45:51.226
[Snoring]

754
00:45:51.357 --> 00:45:54.967
[Passionate moaning]

755
00:45:55.100 --> 00:45:56.930
[Snoring]

756
00:45:57.058 --> 00:45:58.928
[Passionate moaning]

757
00:45:59.060 --> 00:46:02.320
[Snoring]

758
00:46:10.463 --> 00:46:20.343
♪

759
00:46:51.112 --> 00:46:53.292
They're so beautiful.

760
00:46:55.203 --> 00:46:57.683
I'm so glad you like them.

761
00:46:57.815 --> 00:47:00.465
When can I come inside?

762
00:47:03.037 --> 00:47:04.947
♪

763
00:47:05.305 --> 00:48:05.847
